      <head>Oskar Hatschek</head>
      <div>

        <p>Husband of <ref cRef="entity-003244">Klara, <hi rend="italic">née</hi> Schiff</ref>,
          hence brother-in-law of <ref cRef="entity-000771">Jeanette Schenker</ref>; father of <ref
            cRef="entity-008428">Hellmut Hatschek</ref>.</p>

        <p>Oskar was the eldest of the six children of Alexander Hatschek (1855–) and Amalie (1850–;
            <hi rend="italic">née</hi> Steiner). He married <ref cRef="entity-003244">Klara
            Schiff</ref>, sister of <ref cRef="entity-000771">Jeanette Schenker</ref>, and the
          couple had one child, <ref cRef="entity-008428">Hellmut</ref>. Oskar is referred to
          several times in the correspondence between <ref cRef="entity-000944">Rosa Weil</ref> and
          the Schenkers: after the onset of insanity of <ref cRef="entity-003244">Klara</ref>, he
          supported her with stoicism; and once she no longer recognized him he eventually formed a
          new relationship. There is no surviving correspondence between Oskar and the
          Schenkers.</p>
      </div>
